<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Forbes yr shr beats pre-listing forecasts.</title>
<headline>Forbes yr shr beats pre-listing forecasts.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-05-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year ended March 31</p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>Shr, (cts)</p>
<p>    - headline		37.6	  vs 30.1</p>
<p>    - attrib		  37.3	  vs 29.8</p>
<p>    Div (cts)		 18.0	  vs 14.9</p>
<p>    Attrib income	   74.7	  vs 55.5</p>
<p>    Pre-tax		   96.2	  vs 63.2</p>
<p>    Tax rate		  23.5 pct    vs 18.4 pct</p>
<p>    Interest paid	   12.0	  vs 9.7</p>
<p>    Turnover		  624.1	 vs 520.5</p>
<p>Full name: Forbes Group Ltd</p>
<p>NOTE (1)- Directors said that although markets were likely to remain competitive in the new financial year, Forbes was anticipating good growth from its wholly-owned businesses and associates.</p>
<p>They said they expected real growth at the earnings per share level.</p>
<p>NOTE(2)- Forbes shares were listed on the Johannesburg Stock Exchange on November 4, 1996.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
